All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:

**US-002: Hook files shipped in compiled builds**

1. **`src/hooks/embedded.ts`** (new) — Hook scripts embedded as string constants in a `EMBEDDED_HOOKS` map, so they ship with any distribution format (tsc, Bun compile, npm package)

2. **`src/commands/init.ts`** — `copyHooks()` rewritten to use `writeFileSync` from embedded content instead of `copyFileSync` from filesystem. Logs a warning when a hook name isn't found (was silently skipping). Removed unused `__dirname`/`__filename`/`copyFileSync`/`fileURLToPath` imports.

3. **`package.json`** — Added `postbuild` script: `mkdir -p dist/hooks && cp src/hooks/*.sh dist/hooks/` so `.sh` files also appear in `dist/hooks/` after build.

All quality gates pass: typecheck, 67 tests, and build (including postbuild copy). Embedded output verified byte-identical to original `.sh` files.

